The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, June 07, 2004  Calcutta Column

	Shops use silver foil to decorate sweets. But of late, some of the small-scale manufacturers have started using very thin aluminium foil instead, which is supposed to be harmful if consumed. Will the authorities take steps to stop the practice? B.N. Bose, Dum Dum. 
	Ticket checkers fined my co-passengers in the tatkal compartment of the Coromandel Express recently as they did not have proof of identity on them. The railway should display a notice to inform that all the tatkal passengers are expected to carry proof of identity with them during the journey. T.R. Anand, Budge Budge. 
